liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Family and friends have welcomed their loved ones home from the conflict-torn region on the first government-chartered flight into Sydney. In Brisbane, reporter Gemma Ferguson says roughly 100 passengers landed overnight, having transferred from Sydney: Gilad Bino, a Jewish man who grew up in Jerusalem, said he was "emotionally drained by the horrors that have happened in Israel". His family had travelled to Israel to celebrate an aunt's wedding. They were able to return home where he waited to welcome them home with a warm embrace. "The cycle of violence continues unfortunately," he said. "What happened there really shook my core — it was horrible, heartbreaking, to see the extent of violence and hatred." The Brisbane father said he was "really relived" to have his family home, having watched the horror unfold from afar.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Repatriation flights bring Australians back from Israel

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The United States is responsible for the explosion at a Gaza hospital that killed hundreds of Palestinians, Palestinian Hamas leader Ismail Haniyeh said in a televised speech late on Tuesday, stressing that Washington gave Israel "the cover for its aggression." "The hospital massacre confirms the enemy's brutality and the extent of his feeling of defeat," he said, adding that the blast will be "a new turning point." Haniyeh called on all Palestinian people "to get out and confront the occupation and the settlers." He also called on all Arabs, and Muslims to stage protests against Israel. Reporting by Reuters
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Hamas leader blames  US and Israel for blast at Gaza hospital

children.content: The United States is responsible for the explosion at a Gaza hospital that killed hundreds of Palestinians, Palestinian Hamas leader Ismail Haniyeh said in a televised speech late on Tuesday, stressing that Washington gave Israel "the cover for its aggression."
"The hospital massacre confirms the enemy's brutality and the extent of his feeling of defeat," he said, adding that the blast will be "a new turning point."
Haniyeh called on all Palestinian people "to get out and confront the occupation and the settlers."

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Israel's military has denied responsibility for a blast at a Gaza hospital, saying military intelligence suggested the hospital was hit by a failed rocket launch by the enclave's Palestinian Islamic Jihad military group. "An analysis of IDF operational systems indicates that a barrage of rockets was fired by terrorists in Gaza, passing in close proximity to the Al Ahli hospital in Gaza at the time it was hit," a spokesperson for the Israel Defense Forces said in a statement. "Intelligence from multiple sources we have in our hands indicates that Islamic Jihad is responsible for the failed rocket launch which hit the hospital in Gaza." Watch ABC'S Nick Dole's live cross:
